[[${s1q1i1}]]
Exhibit 8 to GDPR Procedures
Data Event Response Framework
1
Data Event Response Framework
Discovery Phase
Step 1: Data Event Occurs
Step 2a: Data Event is discovered by an internal or external source.
Step 2b: Internal source reports the Data Event to the Event Response
Coordinator (ERC): s3q3i1.
Step 2c: External source reports the Data Event to an internal source at
[[${s1q1i1}]] and that internal source reports the Data Event to the ERC.
Reporting Phase
Step 3a: The ERC completes a preliminary version of the Event Report and
submits it to s3q7i1 of the s3q6i1 who has oversite over the Event Response
Process. s3q7i1 determines whether [[${s1q1i1}]] should notify their insurance
agent about the Data Event.
Step 3b: If there is a statutory or contractual duty to notify individuals about
the Data Event, outside or in-house legal counsel draft a notice that complies
with notification obligations. Once the ERC and s3q7i1 approve the notice,
outside or in-house legal counsel oversee the process for delivering notices
to Data Subjects affected by the Data Event. Outside or in-house legal
counsel coordinate [[${s1q1i1}]]'s responses to inquiries about the Data Event.
Step 3c: HR interviews [[${s1q1i1}]]'s employees about the Data Event.
Step 4: The ERC, Security/IT teams, and HR continue gathering facts about
the Data Event until they are satisfied that they have uncovered most, if not
all, the relevant facts about the Data Event.
Recovery Phase
Step 5a: Security/IT teams address network security issues raised by the
Data Event.
Step 5b: HR and Senior Management determine corrective actions for
employees who may have contributed to the Data Event.
Step 6: The ERC finalizes the Event Report, notes any Post-Event Follow Up
items, and submits the final report to s3q7i1 and the s3q6i1.
Step 7: s3q7i1 and the s3q6i1 provide additional notes or guidance, if
applicable, in the Post-Event Follow Up section of the ER.
Step 8: If applicable, the ERC, Security/IT Teams, and HR complete tasks in
2
the Post-Event Follow Up section of the Event Report.
